<div id="review_734480659" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/734480659" />
    <a title="Diane Decorso" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/24465349-diane-decorso"><img alt="Diane Decorso" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/734480659?book_show_action=true">Oct 04, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Diane Decorso" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Diane Decorso" href="/user/show/24465349-diane-decorso">Diane Decorso</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer734480659" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5475085948412621948">Astonishing in its depth of character development and descriptive perceptions, Darshan is an account of multiple generations, living on multiple continents and filled with multiple surprises. In her first novel, Chima has woven together a complex story in such a way that the reader feels a personal and intimate knowledge of, and attachment to, the characters. Her ability to paint a clear picture with her phraseology fills out the story and adds color, profundity and interest at every turn. Chima</span>
  <span id="freeText5475085948412621948" style="display:none">Astonishing in its depth of character development and descriptive perceptions, Darshan is an account of multiple generations, living on multiple continents and filled with multiple surprises. In her first novel, Chima has woven together a complex story in such a way that the reader feels a personal and intimate knowledge of, and attachment to, the characters. Her ability to paint a clear picture with her phraseology fills out the story and adds color, profundity and interest at every turn. Chima’s female characters are independent and fully the strength and core of their families, in spite of existing in a culture where males dominate. Her male characters, while depicted as the expected powerful heads of households, are allowed to experience their own unspoken inner doubts and conflicts as well. She has created a tale that is easy to follow and hard to put down and pure pleasure for the reader from start to finish. You will not want Darshan to end! <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="5475085948412621948" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


