<span id="freeTextContainer12615124107573687903">I really enjoyed reading this book. I identified with the Indian aspects of it, and some parts of it hit close to home (I live in San Francisco). So those two aspects made it intimate.<br/><br/>I enjoyed how the story flowed through generations. The characters were well thought out and realistic. I was even upset with some of them like they were real.<br/><br/>I&apos;m glad this book was recommended to me.</span>
